Dialogs.Dialog: （I know! I wonder if I should invide you to a trip to Hakone ...）
You know, I won a travel again!
Really!? Then, uh... Should we go to another school trip?
However, this time we are on our honeymoon! We'll go on a domestic honeymoon, two days and one night in Hakone!!
Rediscovering domestic honeymoons, one night and 2 days in Hakone.
Oh yeah! By the way, Prez Tezuka will be in the next doubles, right?
...▲高嶺＊＊▲, are you pretending you're not hearing me?
The idea might be old, but I think it's better to go on a honeymoon after getting married...
Hmm... If you're not married, you can't be a newlywed... No, that's not it!
In the 30's of the Showa Era, honeymooners went to Hankone and to Atami.
It seems those places are tour spots for young people to visit once.
Then, you mean... it's just a trip with that theme?
I see... Then, maybe if you feel like it?
（I wonder if I surprised her too much...）
Umm, excuse me? The thing we spoke about before...
If you think about it, it's just a trip to Hakone, right?
Whether it's like a honeymoon, you know, I will like it even if it's the same as usual...
Yes! It's the same as usual.
Alright! Then when should we do it?
Well then, from ▲月▲▲日▲, so our honeymoon lasts for two days and one night!
Ah, then... it's a honeymoon-themed trip to Hakone!
With that kind of theme, I wonder if we'll get along a little more than usual... I'm kidding.
（I did it!! Me and ▲高嶺＊＊▲, together will go on a trip to Hakone!）
（I know! I wonder if I should invite Takane to a trip to Hakone again...）
You know, I actually won a travel prize to our honeymoon again!
Umm, you know... it's a one-night, two-day trip to Hakone.
Hmm, you mean, you're okay with it?
Hmm... it's good because it's like practice. No matter how many times...
Alright! Then when should we do it?
（Let's set the date day. Practice is important...）
Well then, from ▲月▲▲日▲, so our honeymoon lasts for two days and one night!
It's a honeymoon practice trip to Hakone!
（I did it!! Me and ▲高嶺＊＊▲, together will go on a trip to Hakone!）
Um, it's a trip, but you see, this time...
Yes, our honeym-- No, our trip to Hakone, right?
Yes. Why don't we go shopping?
It's okay, but... It's one night, right? Do you need something?
Hmm? I wondering if it's better to practice a little in that place...
Very well then... let's go practice, okay??
If it was a real honeymoon, why don't we look for what we need?
Yes, I undertand... OK, let's go!
Alright, is it something like this?
I wonder about it, I found one. Two people can make one big bag.
Ah, that's right! Is it the same as packing to go home as newlyweds?
Yes... And I'm sure we'll pack together in the future.
This practice was fun. I'm looking forward to our trip, more and more.
Oh, I still have something to do... Can you go back first?
Are you going to do some real shopping?
Yes, my practice for shopping is not over yet...
Then, want me to go with you?
No, that's fine! It's individual practice... Bye bye.
（I'm sure she will look into bride stuff...）
（▲高嶺＊＊▲, I wonder if you have already arrived... Ah!）
▲高嶺＊＊▲! Good morning. Did I make you wait?
Even so, it's already hot and humid in the mornings...
Fufu, it's June. Hey~, how do you say June is Japanese?
Well, since it's June, I'll say something...
Ah, isn't it a little cold in the mornings?
Hmm, I'm sure Hakone is a little more. Besides, there will be autumn leaves.
It'll be good if it happens... Even of it's practice, it's nice to be romantic...
It's because is my first time.
Your first time going to Hakone?
Yes, it's a romancecar▼ When I went with my family, we went by car.
Ah, this is... Umm, a ３００００-type ＥＸＥ!
He~e, it has that kind of shape.
Hmm. It's a 6th generation, and it's the most common form used for commuting.
I see, I'm riding the ＥＸＥ... Fufu~♪
（This is not a honeymoon- like conversation...）
Are you looking forward to the "Romacecar" so much?
Umm, of course, not only that, but also Hakone...
Well, but riding a limited express is also fun!
That's right! Are you looking forward to ride the "Romancecar"?♪
Yes, the ３００００-type. Hey, let's ride it!
（▲高嶺＊＊▲, you get so excited when it comes to trains...）
Really! Hey~, do you feel lonely?
The sheet is wide, so we're a little far way, right?
But I'm not lonely, because I don't have an armrest♪ Fufu▼
Hmm... I like the limited express!
Yeah, even though the seats are wide, and I feel a little lonely!
Yes▼ You're not lonely anymore, right? Fufu~!
Ah, Mt. Fuji! It looks a lot closer...
It's like that time at Atami...
Did you do it when we traveled to Atami? Pretending to be on a honeymoon.
This time... what are you going to do? Because this is a practice trip...
What do you wanna do ▲高嶺＊＊▲?
Did you do it when we traveled to Atami? Pretending to be on a honeymoon.
Ah... you were referring to that.
But this trip is "practice", and what about it...
What do you wanna do ▲高嶺＊＊▲?
（It's a little embarrassing, but let's so our best...）
Perhaps we have been doing it since the time we went to Atami.
Hmm, if you think about it, you might be right.
Okay, let's practice a lot this time as well▼
We will soon arrive at the end point, Hakone Yumoto. For the Hakone Tozan Line and Gora...
Look, Hakone Yumoto. There are a few stops left, so it's closer.
So many shops lined up all the time... It's amazing...
Okay, what should we do first?
Hmm... not that, I meant something related to our practice...
Ah, I see... So what then?
Ha~a～! Were here, in Hakone again!
When we arrived in Hakone, I remembered all the colors... from our last honeymoon.
（Even though it's been too long, I'm still shy...）
The Hydrangea Bridge. You can see well Hayakawa...
Oh, there in a hydrangea on the riverbank...
In June, Hakone will entertain tourists throughout town.
And with that, can we see more?
Yes, I'm sure it'll be fun▼
It's the "Hydrangea bridge". Isn't the hydrangea blooming?
Fufu, yes. But, can you see? There are leaves instead...
A mountain of autumn leaves for the honeymoon...
Yes, maybe we rediscovered it. A honeymoon in Hakone.
I hope we can see a lot of autumn leaves in Hakone.
It's a little early, but let's eat lunch around this place.
Is there anything you want to eat?
Hmm... can we have soba? Since we came all the way to Hakone.
Soba, huh. Okay, let's go find some!
Yes, how about we check around here? Would you like to go there? To "Hatsuhana".
Ah, it seems to have history behind it!
It's thriving with people... Is it a famous store?
Yes, that's right. It was introduced on TV... Did you read the store description?
The soba here is kneaded with yam and eggs without using water.
Sorry to keep you waiting, here is your "Sadajo Soba" and your "Tempura Soba".
Oh!? It's delicious! What do you think ▲高嶺＊＊▲?
"Sadajo Soba", huh? I wonder if I should order that...
If we're newlyweds, isn't it natural to do it...?
Thank you for the food, it was delicious.
Shall we have lunch before going to the "Hakone Glass Forest Museum"?
Yeah, since we came to Hakone, why don't we go to "Hatsuhana" again?
▲高嶺＊＊▲, you seriously like that place, right? Alright, let's go!
Wow, it looks like it's crowded today...
Sorry to keep you waiting. Here is your "Sadajo Soba" and your "Tendon".
▲高嶺＊＊▲, did you ask for the same dish from last time?
Certainly, it's delicious! Yeah... I wonder if I should have done it too...
Geez~, once again? Then, want to try mine?
It's because my husband wants to eat it...
Next is the "Hakone Glass Forest Museum".
Then, we'll have to go to the Hakone Tozan Railway, right? To Gora we go!
Ah, a １０００-type! Umm... it's a Bernina!
He~e! So this vehicle has a name. You sure know your stuff...
I just happened to know it... I know, hey~, can we go see the watering tank?
Hey~, we're going to the Hakone Tozan Railway next, right?
Yes, to get to "Hakone Glass Forest Museum" we have to go to Gora.
Hmm... When you told me, I remembered it.
Right? I'm in your care again. Do your best, Bernina♪
80 per mile... Even though it's a train, it can go so fast...
That's... Yeah, it's definitely amazing. Look, the hydrangea is also beautiful, right?
Really, a lot of blowers are in bloom... I'm glad we came in a good season.
Ah, look! It's almost time to switch!
Hey~, you can see it when you climb the mountain of autumn leaves by train like this, right?
In case of emergency, we need a rail crimping brake...
We arrived! The last stop, Gora station!
Yes... it's a little cold after all.
It's a mountain railway, right? Look, the station building looks like a mountain lodge.
That's right! Now then, let's go to "Hakone Glass Forest Museum".
Yes, let's take a bus, right?
Yes, correct... Do you hate buses, ▲高嶺＊＊▲?
Can you say to me "Come here"?
We arrived! The last stop, Gora Station!
Ugh, it's a little cold... the wind is a little strong.
It seems that there used to be an outdoor skating rink...
Now we have to take a bus to "Hakone Glass Forest Museum", right?
I know, do you want to take a break?
I'm alright. You see, if you do it...
▲高嶺＊＊▲, we'll get there soon, do your best!
Hmm. I'm glad to be together with my gentle husband.
Did it look like it was shaking?
Next is the Tawarashi/Hakone Glass Forest...
We have arrived to Hakone Forest Glass Museum. Customers who get off should not forget anything...
Wow... It's made of stone and looks like a real old castle.
And see over there! A glass tree!
It's glittering! I see, it's a glass forest!
Please enjoy while taking your time.
Look at this ticket! It has an interesting shape.
We have arrived to Hakone Forest Glass Museum. Customers who get off should not forget anything...
We arrived at "Hakone Glass Forest Museum"!
The glass tree is so beautiful today...
Even if you know that's the reflection of the sun, it's mysterious...
Please enjoy while taking your time.
Did you see? This ticket changed compared to last time. Does it change depending on the season?
It seems so. It's still too elaborated, though...
It's beautiful... The whole building seems like the exact image of Venice.
Speaking of which, the Venetian flag is at the entrance... But it's glittering, and more――
It's like a fairy tail world... Look, it's like the princess and prince are coming out.
It's a hydrangea made of glass...
It's called "Hortensia" and it's made up to 2,000 pieces of glass.
Fufu! Hey~, did you see? There are many other hydrangeas in bloom!
Oh, the grass of glass is...
Oh... one hundred pieces of glass... 100 pieces!?
It's autumn in the country of glass. Fufu~♪
A corridor of light... Crystal glass, let's see... 160,000 parts!?
Fufu, it's swaying in the wind and glittering, it's beautiful...
Hey~, when you pass through, you're supposed to be a prince and a princess, right?
You're fine as the princess, but should I be the prince?
Well then... Shall we go visit, princess?
▲高嶺＊＊▲, do you like what you see here?
It's because... This is what you see at the end of the story, right?
Something like "And they lived happily forever."
I imagined it since I as little. Where will you live? I asked myself.
Did you imagined this kind of place?
It's called "Hortensia", and it says it uses 2,000 pieces of glass.
Fufu! Hey~, did you see? There are many other hydrangeas in bloom!
It's autumn in the country of class. Fufu~♪
It's shining today too... it's dazzling.
Hey, can we do it again?
Okay then... Shall we go visit, princess?
Look, a chandelier! It's like a castle hall!
It looks fine! Is that a "Millefiori"?
It seems to mean "thousand flowers". It's a mosaic glass technique from ancient Rome.
Stretching the glass out, making patterns smaller and smaller... it's amazing...
A "Globet with dot-colored flower lid". It looks like from around the 16th century...
I wonder if I can put something in and drink from it...
What is this? It looks heavy, but... Ah, look at it from behind――
The light coming from it is cobalt blue. It's beautiful...
And over here, is that the museum shop?
Wow! Can we take a look?
There seems to be various things... Ah, is that a "Millefiori"?
It's like combining glasses and melting them together. It sounds interesting...
I did it... Hmm, is this really beautiful?
It took about 70 minutes to make.
Want to take a break at the restaurant?
It's the "Cafe Terrazza". It's amazing! It even has live music.
Fufu~, is it called "Canzone"? It feels like we're in Italy, right?
Sorry to keep you waiting. Here is your fuit tea.
Wow, this has lots of fruit!
There is plenty for two people!
Okay, can you lend me a cup? Shall we drink together? Right, Dear▼
Here, sorry to keep you waiting. It's finished very beautifully, right?
Thank you very much. Oh, it's beautiful.
We still have some time left so, want to look around a little more?
Look, a glass fountain! Fontana, huh...
Oh... There are 45,000 glass pieces. I'm not surprised.
Fufu~! Ah, hey~, over there. Huh, what is that?
There seems to be no explanation in particular...
It's like a bell to ring together. Hey~, can we ring it?
But, what wish can we make on it?
（Then, what I will wish for with ▲高嶺＊＊▲）
▲高嶺＊＊▲, what did you wish for?
Umm... It's a secret. But I'm sure it's the same as yours.
Yeah, this is a real honeymoon...
Look, it's the Fontana! The Glass Fountain! It's glittering.
I know, do you want to ring the "Oath Bell"?
Yes, I also want to wish again. Fufu~!
... Hmm. Have you decided your wish?
（Okay, what I will wish for with ▲高嶺＊＊▲...）
Hey~, shall we learn something new tomorrow?
We had so much fun it the Glass Forest...
▲高嶺＊＊▲, did you like it that much?
Yes... When I was there, I felt like one of my childhood dreams had come true.
I see. I'm glad for you, right?
The bus has arrived, let's go!
Are you okay going by bus?
I'm fine, I was just thinking for a minute.
I wonder if a true honeymoon is happier that this. I can't imagine it...
Next is the end point, Togendai, Togendai. Hakone Ropeway, the sea...
Wow, I can see Lake Ashi!
We're goin to board a ship tomorrow, right? A pirate ship!
Yes, today we're just staying at the hotel, though.
It's nothing... I just remembered... We're newlyweds.
（When you say that, I get kinda nervous...）
Hey, you can see it from here! The "Hakone Lake Hotel"!
Ah, I see. Well then... Aika, come here?
We arrived at the "Hakone Lake Hotel"!
Wow... It looks like a foreign hotel... There is also a large chandelier.
It'll be okay... I'll just go check-in.
Maybe we can use the same last name, you know, like practice since we're together...
Sorry to keep you waiting. I think I wrote it properly, “▲苗字▲ Aika”, like this.
Sorry to keep you waiting. Now then, I will explain the facilities in the hall.
Please go here with you wife.
Did you write it right? It's “▲苗字▲ Aika”.
Sorry to keep you waiting. Then, I will explain the facilities in the hall.
Please go here with you wife.
I wonder if I did it well... I'm kidding.
The room is a Japanese-style room.
I'm glad. To tell you the truth, I was a little nervous...
We can relax on the tatami mats!
Yes, fufu~! Oh, you can see the mountains very close from this window!
It's true. Well then, should we lay out the futons ourselves?
The futon... Ah, yeah, I'll do it... It's for practice.
My house doesn't have Japanese-style rooms, so I like this kind of thing.
With a small table, brewing tea with my husband... I would like it.
We still have some time left... Do you want to take a bath first?
The men's bath is "heaven" and women's bath is "sky"... Oh, there is an open-air bath!
As newlyweds, we should go in together...
Geez~, then, I'll meet you at the lobby, okay?
The open-air bath is so good!...
Is it over there too? Emm, it looks like a coccon...
Coccon? Ah, it's over here too!
What is that? It's lighting ...Hey, I'll check it out!
Hello～～o. I come to make my report～. It was a sauna～.
There is lighting inside, it's very fashionable~.
He~e! Would you like to go in?
Ha~a～～... The hot water was so good.
Don't look at me that much...
Geez... Hey, can we take a walk back to the hotel?
Okay then... Huh, what are you doing?
He~e, there's even a relaxation room.
I want to enter! Can I?
Ha~a～... We're going to be fluffy, right? Fufu♪
Ah, it's didn't work... Then, next――
A souvenir corner! Hey, can we go?
Is that a Hakone specialty? There are a lot of things...
Those parquets look beautiful! It's so nice...
Do you want to buy sweets?
Ah, truly. Gotoji themed? Also manjuus, and cookies...
Hey~, are you hungry? Do you want to eat something?
Did you get hungry when you saw the sweets?
It's because... you're so mean, my husband.
Wow... this place gives out an adult-like feeling, isn't it?
Sorry to keep you waiting. Here you have your "Sanzoku-yaki made of pork loin".
Really. But I'm so hungry already...
▲高嶺＊＊▲, did you eat that much?
Then, do you want some of mine?
Please, eat a lot my husband? Okay, open wide▼
Thank you so much for the food. I'm so full...
Are you okay? I'm sure I did eat my share...
I'm fine, I'll just take a break!
Then, can you lie down? I'll give you a massage. Ah, but a while ago――
No, no! By all means, please.
Fufu~♪ Hmm～～, I'm good at this~... Then, how's this? *Rub, rub*♪
▲高嶺＊＊▲, your massages are so good!
Can I be a good wife now? Fufu~!
Ah... Hey~, why don't we go see the lake before it's late?
You're right, we haven't gone there. Let's go!
Geez, it's already night, right? Ah, the hotel...
Oh, it's all lit up, right?
Hmm, it's nice... Hey, shall we go?
Yes... Instead, you can see the lights outside, and those are beautiful...
Hey~, in this case, what is a good topic to talk about?
It's about the future. What would you like, a boy or a girl?
I like... Hmmm, both actually. And as many as possible.
Yes, getting up early every morning, making breakfast and wake you and the children...
Fufu~, then can you help me?
I like to be always with the family. Everyone eating breakfast, and taking baths...
I like that, it sounds good...
So when the kids go to bed, I'll go back with my lover. Just like us now...
It's night already... Hey, shall we go?
Well ride it again tomorrow, right?
When I went to see the front, I saw a Papa and Mama with lots of kids.
Both of them were hugging a baby, and were holding the hands of the little kids.
Eh~? Umm, can't you imagine it?
Fufu, I can imagine it. You where holding the hand of a little kid.
You would be a nice Papa, right? I'm sure Mama will be happy... I'm kidding.
Even if we become Papa and Mama, let's always do this, right?
There is a promenade over there...
Eh, right now!? Shouldn't we stop? It's dark, isn't it dangerous?
It feels like it wouldn't be strange if something came out of that bush...
Ah, the promenade!... Do you want to go in?
It's because you're trying to scare me...
I won't do it! Come here, Aika?
In movies, a man with an ax suddenly pops out from the sides, right?
It's alright, it's only the tree branches!
Geez~, meanie! Don't be like that my husband!
Now then... It's too early to go to bed, should we lay out the futon first?
Ah, then should I lay them?
No, it's for practice. It a wife's job, right?
No, no, it's hard work. I'll do it!
Hey~... I feel like our futons are closer...
That so... I don't think so? You know, we're newly married!
Can I take a bath again?
I was sweating when I was walking outside.
It was cold around the lake, so I wanted to sleep a little after warming up.
（Fu~... don't get me wrong, it's practice for our honeymoon...）
Well, then I'll see you soon, right?
Can I enter the sauna? Isn't it a little late?
Okay! Then, can I go with you?
Ah, it feels good... Ha~a～, I'm in heaven...
I had a dream!! I was really going to heaven...
What's wrong? We're taking too long in the bath, right?
Aren't you dazed? Your face is a little red...
（I should stop taking naps in the hot springs...）
（I don't have anything else to do, should I go to sleep? ▲高嶺＊＊▲ is...）
Shall we go to bed soon? Isn't it time to finish practicing?
I sometimes think that my way of thinking is old...
But, if you feel the same... Then, I'm happy.
I love you because you're kind.
Hey~, can we talk after getting into the futon?
（Okay... we don't have anything else to do, I'll just turn off the lights and go to bed...）
Are you going to sleep? Isn't it time to finish practicing?
I want a goodnight kiss. I'm kidding... Fufu▼
（I'm glad I got up early, because I slept properly yesterday!）
Fufu♪ You're sleeping well～ It's almost time for breakfast, okay～?
Hmm, I feel a little sorry for this... Here it goes～?
This is also a wife's duty. Did you wake up? Dear▼
Geez~... you did it on purpose, pervert...
Breakfast will be served soon. Please change your clothes soon, my husband?
It's alright... Sorry to keep you waiting, it's okay now, okay?
Breakfast will be served soon. Please change your clothes soon, my husband?
Huh? Wait a minute! I'm seeing your back!
Ah... the scent of freshly baked bread...
Did you also take a lot, ▲高嶺＊＊▲?
It's all good♪ You have to eat a lot in the morning. Don't we have a lot of things to do today?
Hey~, having breakfast on the terrace like this, you see...
It's like being on a honeymoon?
Yes, I was longing for it.
I see, I'm glad for you, right? Okay, let's eat.
Yay! Then, since we're newlyweds, open wide, ah~▼
Thank you for chosing us. We look forward to seeing you again.
Alright... We didn't forget anything, right?
"Hakone Lake Hotel" is such a comfortable hotel.
Hmm, I hope we can come again... Hey~, why don't we take a photo?
Good! Then, we'll go to Owakudani's ropeway right now!
Sorry to keep you waiting! I bought the tickets.
Thank you. Hey~, huh, did you see that?
Look, there are two ropes. We're going on that rope...
It's nice, it's such a big machine...
Don't admire the place... C'mon, let's line up!
It's such a nice weather today, so we can enjoy a walk in the sky!
Ah, I see... You're not good at looking down?... Are you okay?
I'm fine. My husband is with me, I'm kidding.
Smoke is coming out from the ground! Look, can you see it!
... You're not doing fine, are you okay?
I-I'm fine. It's a little expensive... I'm kidding.
You're not doing fine in high places... Aika, come here?
Thank you. I'm glad I have a reliable husband▼
Soon, we will arrive at Owakudani Station. Rope to Sounzan will...
Oh... it's a wonderful view... Are you okay, ▲高嶺＊＊▲?
If I do this, I'll be fine.
Hey~, can you see? Mt. Fuji looks so big...
Soon, we will arrive at Owakudani Station. Rope to Sounzan will...
Amazing... I think this place was used to be called Jigokudani...
Yes, it's amazing... does it smell like hydrogen sulfide?
You add hydrochloric acid to iron sulfide, right? Didn't you try it as an experiment in junior high?
The hot springs are carried by steel pipes with a total lenght of ２６００ｍ, with a height difference of ３５０ｍ...
Ha~a～! I see... Would you like to see more?
Amazing... a lot of smoke is coming from the ground. It's an active volcano...
Fufu~, it's nice♪ Let's hurry up!
Yes, hydrogen sulfide reacts with iron to form iron sulfide... that's how the black egg is made...
（This seems more like a chemistry class...）
The steam is amazing... It can keep boiling water at 80 degress Celsius...
You need 1 cal to raise 1 cc of water at once, right? That means...
How much heat will it have? After all――
Um... Would you like to go see other places?
Show it to me! Oh, it's really black! Amazing!
I wonder if it has iron sulfide.
...Hmm? Well, maybe... No matter how it looks――
Alright, let's eat! It's hot, so be careful.
Yes... I'm thrilled, but I'm relieved to do this...
This is what a honeymoon is like... I'm kidding▼
Soon, we will arrive at Togendai Station. Hakone Pirate Ship, Hakone Town...
It's a little early, but can we have lunch here before boarding the pirate ship?
Okay, want to do it near a place facing the lake?
Oh... There are various menus! Which one do you want?
Me? Emm, well then... Hmm? Huh! This one!
Ginger saute. The pork looks delicous.
He~e... Looks like a kind of special pig. Does it looks delicious?
Is it that good? Can you eat them all?
Can you help me? I can't eat it all. Okay, say ah~♪
Today I'll have a cutlet curry, with salad.
It's delicious♪ But, it's a little too much, so can you help me?
Oh you... You want to eat it all!
Really? It's true! Hey, can you help me?
Wow, take a look! It's amazing!
Oh, it looks so powerful when you look at it!
It's big~... Is it full- scale?
I think so... It's very well done!
Mushaburui. I remembered a book about pirates I read when I was in elementary school. Hey, can we get on?
It's so big... The total lenght is ３５ｍ, or ３１５ｔ...
Huh? Yeah, somehow... Isn't it something newlyweds do?
Umm... I don't remember the speed.
Oh, 3D art of pirate paintings! It looks it can pop out!
I was looking for the place to see the engine! It has two 575 horsepower engines!
Hey~, why don't we go out to the deck and take a photo?
Ha~a... it's a good feeling ...wide, like the sea...
When I was a kid, every time a pirate appeared in a book, I thought I was a boy....
Because it's hard to imagine a girl becoming a pirate.
That's right. But now I feel like I'm a pirate. Fufu♪
From here, it's a short walk to Hakone Shrine, right? Did you see the torii from the ship?
Ah, look, I can see it!
It's really built in the water.
We are welcoming the Dragon God from the lake. You see, it's facing the lake.
It was built in １９５２ to commemorate the San Francisco Peace Treaty...
